euclidext

Class Result

  • java.lang.Object
    • euclidext.Result

  •  class Result
extends java.lang.Object
    A structure desinged to support Euclid's Extended Algorithm. The data is in the form A*M+B*N=D where A=coeff1, M=input1, B=coeff2, N=input2, and D=gcd

      • setError

        public void setError(java.lang.String err)
        An error has been encountered. This will set all generated values to 0 (coeff1, coeff2, and gcd) as well as set the errorFlag to true. The generated error message should be passed in as a parameter.
